<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Medication Contraindication Checker</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css" />
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <div class="header-content">
      <h1>Medication Contraindication Checker</h1>
      <span class="badge">SMART-on-FHIR Training</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="landing">
    <div class="card hero-card">
      <h2>Welcome</h2>
      <p>
        This app demonstrates a <strong>SMART-on-FHIR</strong> launch flow
        combined with <strong>SNOMED CT terminology queries</strong> to detect
        medication contraindications based on a patient's allergies.
      </p>

      <div class="how-it-works">
        <h3>How it works</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>Launch from an EHR or the <a href="https://launch.smarthealthit.org" target="_blank">SMART Launcher</a></li>
          <li>Retrieve the patient's medications and allergies via FHIR</li>
          <li>Extract active ingredients using SNOMED CT ECL on a terminology server</li>
          <li>Check each ingredient against each allergy using <code>$validate-code</code></li>
          <li>Display any detected contraindications</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="launch-instructions">
        <h3>Launch Instructions</h3>
        <p>To test this app:</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Go to <a href="https://launch.smarthealthit.org" target="_blank">launch.smarthealthit.org</a></li>
          <li>Set the <strong>App Launch URL</strong> to: <code id="launch-url"></code></li>
          <li>Select a patient (or use the test patient you created)</li>
          <li>Click <strong>Launch</strong></li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <footer>
    <p>Developer Training Exercise &mdash; FHIR R4 + SNOMED CT</p>
  </footer>

  <script>
    // Display the launch URL dynamically based on current host
    document.getElementById("launch-url").textContent =
      window.location.origin + "/launch";
  </script>
</body>
</html>
